Title: The Reeh-Schlieder property for thermal field theories

Authors: Christian Jaekel

Comments: plain tex, 10 pages

Journal-ref: J.Math.Phys. 41 (2000) 1745-1754

We show that the Reeh-Schlieder property w.r.t. the KMS-vector is a directconsequence of locality, additivity and the relativistic KMS-condition. Thelatter characterises the thermal equilibrium states of a relativistic quantumfield theory. The statement remains vaild even if the given equilibrium statebreaks spatial translation invariance.